<br>
1. Don't solo, but if you do expect to get ganked from time to time.  I don't care what class you are (yes     dr00ds and necros too) if you are alone you are much more vunerable.<br>
<br>
2. Don't trust anyone except your GOOD friends.  This means not wearing equipment you don't want to    lose around people you don't know and just being generally skeptical and aware of what people are    doing.  There's nothing worse then being lulled into a false sense of security and then coming back    from LD pked and looted by your own group member.<br>
<br>
3. PVP can be fun but the best revenge is to get exp.  Yup, you just lost a really nice item or a lot of pp     to some ganker, but wasting a bunch of time seeking revenge will get you nowhere.  Most of the time     you won't even get the satisfaction of looting them for anything.  Plus there is always better loot at     higher lvls so move on.<br>
<br>
4. Avoid crowded areas to exp.  Make friends and go to underpopulated and obscure places to exp.  It    may be easy to get a group in those crowded zones but you can never equip safely and you are always    looking over your shoulder.<br>
<br>
5. If you don't need to be wearing your equipment stay bagged.  There's no good reason to be running       around in your phat lewtz if you don't need to be.<br>
<br>
6. /guildstatus I had no idea this command existed for way too long..  Guildstatus everyone!<br>
<br>
7. If someone is a known pker don't let them hang out and watch you exp.  Kill them before they kill you.     I can't believe how many groups just let someone wait for them to get low on health and mana.  Kill        the pker and chase them off.  You might have to do this a few times but generally they give up.<br>
<br>
8. All gnomes are dirty bastards! lol =)<br>
<br>
Hmm, that's it for now.  Comments? Additions? Discussion?<br>
<br>
Shiris, 52 Wanderer<br>
Nimbly, 24 Rogue<br>
